<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-492-887  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 492 887.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Journal of Object-Oriented Programming  Sept-Oct 1990 v3 n3p11(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Design and implementation of an object-oriented, strongly typedlanguage for distributed applications. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Krakowiak, S.; Meysembourg, M.; Nguyen Van, H.; Riveill, M.;andO;Roisin, C.; Rousset de Pina, X.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Guide is a language for the programming of distributedapplications; its runtime support is supplied by anobject-oriented distributed operating system also called Guide.andO;The characteristics of an object model implemented in Guide are:objects are typed; a class defines a specific implementation of atype; subtyping defines a hierarchy of types; and objects arepersistent.andP;  Guide supports concurrency.andP;  Experience with theprototype of Guide shows the flexibility provided by dynamicbinding and subtyping can be combined with the safety provided bystrong typing and compile time checking; location transparency canbe supplied for persistent objects supported by the language; asynchronization mechanism can be designed that is fully compatiblewith the object model; and the separation between type and classcombines the advantages of inheritance and data abstraction.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Object-Oriented LanguagesDistributed SystemsProgrammingDesignImplementation.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Execution structures. (chart)Structure of the Mail application. (chart)Run-time representation of an object. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>